column5: I fished 9 this year, I listed them in order from most fished to least.  Georgian Bay (Victoria Harbour) Buckhorn Pigeon Simcoe Scugog Rice Little Bald Chemong Lake Ontario  my favorite had to be Georgian Bay.

i have a big list circle lk twin lakes twinline lakes penache lake augusta lake mud lake delaney lake depensier lake apsey lake brazil lake lake 12 bird lake boundary lake may lake pawson lake elizabeth lake constant lake triangle lake sausage lake mink lake tea lake glassy lake south river lake nipissing i guess 24 that i can think of most of which are for bass wallies or speckle trout
i think i forgot to mention the mattawa and ottawa rivers
Big Doe, Rice Lake, Rainy Lake, Lake Erie, Grand River (hated it) Cameron Lake, Sturgeon Lake. A real tour of the classics. Jim

sneaky way of tricking people into listing their secret lake ! lol  Not as many as I wanted to !!  Nipigon Jackpine Slitzig Side Rock Spawning Sunrise Big Bear Temagami Nipissing GBay BOQ Simcoe Silver Lake on hwy7

East Lake, Kesagami Lake, Kesagami River, Five Mile Lake, Five Mile River, Patawanimau, Lillibelle, Unknown River, Booth, Crotch, Robin, Shall, Opeongo River, Rye Grass, Kitty Lake, Farm Lake, Scugog, Steenburg, Robinson, Pine, BOQ, Moira River, R. Creek, Outlet River, Tatler, Potters Creek, Lake Ontario, Madawaska River, Papinau Creek and Black Creek.  Even 30 this year.  -R-

Hmmm...not too many now that I think back...  Sturgeon Scugog Chemong Lake O Lake St Clair Lake Nipissing The lake where Solopaddler's cottage is, and a few back lakes in the area. 2 back lakes north of Cochrane, again with Solopaddler...cant remember the names.... Ahmic Lake Fishnsled's secret muskie lake...LOL Bay of Quinte...although I suppose technically you could call that Lake O.  I'm sure I'm forgetting a few!!!
4+  Chemong, Buckhorn, maybe they don't count (about 1/2 day total) Scugog and Lake O. (regularly) Several lakes and ponds I saw while driving   forrest

For me it's 8  Lake I can't remember for speckle trout early spring Lac poisson Blanc Lac St-Marie Lac Le Blanc Ottawa river Bay McLauren Lac Leamay Another lake I can't remember for SMB & Pike  Leechman
Hrm..  A lake here a lake there.. Never really kept count.  I would say about 5-6 different lakes and a crapload of rivers/streams.

Elliot Lake lake #2 fridgid digit elephant flying goose Pecors VanHorn dunlop ten mile bierce kindiogami good lookin loon location bolgers lake #23 big quirke little quirke flack hough mccarthy trout depot spanish river north channel of Lake Huron Ivanhoe white river and few few other speck lakes I'll keep to myself!  Not a bad year!
Lake Wahnapitae ...24 lbs Northern Pike, 22 Lbs Lake Trout. 11 Lbs Walleye, 4 lbs. Smallmouth and 13 inch Jumbos Prech ...Why go anywhere else
Why would you fish anywhere else?  That astounds me!  You do any guiding?

Lake Erie - Smallies Lake Ontario - Smallies / Largies Upper Niagara - Smallies / Largies Hamilton Harbour - Largies Nine Mile Lake - Largies Simcoe - Largies / Smallies Couch - Largies / Smallies Lower Niagara - Steelies Lake Gibson - Pike Lake Moody - Pike Beaver Lake (Tamworth) - Mixed Bag Cattaragus Creek - Steelies Olcott (what a mess) - I don't know Lake Wilcox - Largies  And a few other smaller Lakes and Creeks  It's been a good year, and you can probably tell I mostly fish for bass.

didn't really hit up many lakes/rivers this year, always stuck with the ones close to home.  lake scugog balsam lake buckhorn lake cameron lake rice lake chemong lake  grand river oshawa creek bowmanville wilmot duffins big head river beaver river nottawasaga river
Y'know, a little here, a little there. Mostly Lake Erie.

I don't normally find the need to hit too many different lakes over the season  A couple different K lakes  Quinte  3 trips to the West Arm of Nippissing  Babaganouche  St. Lawrence River  St. Clair  And today we'll close the musky season on the Niagara
Lake Seymour Lake Scugog Lyndhusrt Lake Stoney Lake Bass Lake Baptist Lake Elephant Lake

A little bit of variety...but not compared to most on here...  Upper Buckhorn Chemong Pigeon Little Bald Big Bald Limerick Coon Big Cedar Bass Crotch Simcoe Couchaching  ...that's about it. Better then most years when I never leave the Tri-Lakes.

Didn't really think about this before but fished only two lakes this season. Pigeon Lake (warm season) Lake Ontario(cold season)  Fished a few river systems (Credit, Saugeen) for little brook trout as well.

Chemong Upper Buckhorn Lower Buckhorn Pigeon Big Bald Little Bald Sturgeon Thanks to Big Cliff Rice Stoney Lovesick Fairy Clear Katchewanooka Trent River  Wow after thinking this through I sure got around!
Forgot about Little Bald, almost seems like an extension of Pigeon. So then there is three.
The usual ones, such as:  Buckhorn Scugog Simcoe Lake O Rice  and another 10 or so in the Parry Sound area
Balsam lake Cameron Lake Sturgeon Lake Simcoe  Steelheading in creeks near GTA.

Well lets see:  scugog sturgeon [20 times] pigeon bay of quinte  [8times] lake ontario  [30 times] at least crystal lake salerno lake white lake ottawa river lake clear gooderham lake petawawa river black bay rice lake trent river ottanabe river  and i know that there is more,that im forgetting ???? its interesting to see where everyone was fishing,man we all sure put on the miles dont we !!!! cheers....
